properties.description1:
The objective of the Second Secondary Education Development Program Project (SEDP II) for Tanzania is to improve the quality of secondary education with a focus on underserved areas. The main project development objectives are the followings:
(i) Increase in the number of secondary schools meeting minimum infrastructure requirements
(ii) Improvements in the equitable provision of teachers and the quality of teaching in mathematics, sciences, and languages
(iii) Providing capacity building and technical assistance to implement reforms.

Approval Date: May 27, 2010
Closing Date: December 31, 2016
Total Project Cost: US$ 469.30 million
Commitment Amouint US$ 150.00 million

-Click for the results-

The development objective of Tanzania's Zanzibar Basic Education Improvement Project is to improve completion of lower secondary education with successful performance among students. The project aims to support the construction of nineteen new schools; support the in-service training of teachers of mathematics and science; purchase and distribution of secondary school textbooks in four subjects for all students in secondary school and textbooks for science subjects; support for science education for girls and provision of life skills, including HIV/AIDS, gender and environmental awareness; and revision of primary curriculum and provisions of appropriate learning materials. The main indicators to assess the project are the followings:
(i) Pupils/Classrooms ratio
(ii) Percentage of qualified teachers

Approval Date: April 24, 2007
Closing Date: November 30, 2013
Total Project Cost: US$ 48.00 million
Commitment Amount: US$ 42.00 million

-Click for the results-

The objective of the Big Results Now in Education Program (BRNEd) Project is to improve education quality in Tanzanian secondary schools. The main project development objectives are the followings:
(i) Increasing the national average performance in reading and numeracy,
(ii) Higher percentage of teachers found in classrooms during unannounced visit in secondary schools
(iii) Improvements in student performance on Certificate of Secondary Education Examination (CSEE).

Approval Date: July 10, 2014
Closing Date: January 31, 2020
Total Project Cost: US$ 416.00 million
Commitment Amount: US$ 122.00million
